# Chapter 3: The Shepherd's Lesson

## Story

### The Young Shepherd

![A young shepherd boy standing on a hillside with a flock of sheep, holding a wooden staff, with Hebrew text "רעה" (shepherd) and "צאן" (flock) visible on a pastoral landscape](young-shepherd-boy-hillside-flock-sheep-wooden-staff-hebrew-text-roeh-tzon-pastoral-landscape)

בָּהָר יָשַׁב רֹעֶה צָעִיר. שְׁמוֹ הָיָה שִׁמְעוֹן. רָעָה שִׁמְעוֹן אֶת הַצֹּאן. הָיָה רֹעֶה טוֹב מְאֹד. רָעָה הַצֹּאן בַּיּוֹם וְרָעָה בַּלַּיְלָה.

### The Sheep See a Wolf

![A flock of white sheep on a green hillside suddenly looking alert and frightened as they spot a grey wolf in the distance, with Hebrew text "ראה" (see) and "זאב" (wolf) visible](flock-white-sheep-green-hillside-alert-frightened-grey-wolf-distance-hebrew-text-raah-zeev)

יוֹם אֶחָד רָאוּ הַכְּבָשִׂים זְאֵב רָחוֹק. רָאֲתָה כִּבְשָׂה אַחַת וְקָרְאָה: "רְאוּ! זְאֵב!" רָאוּ כָּל הַכְּבָשִׂים אֶת הַזְּאֵב. הֵן רָאוּ וְיָרְאוּ מְאֹד.

### The Sheep Are Afraid

![The same flock of sheep huddled together, trembling with fear, their eyes wide with terror as they continue to watch the wolf, with Hebrew text "ירא" (fear) prominently displayed](flock-sheep-huddled-together-trembling-fear-eyes-wide-terror-watching-wolf-hebrew-text-yarei)

יָרְאוּ הַכְּבָשִׂים מִן הַזְּאֵב. יָרְאָה כָּל כִּבְשָׂה. הֵן יָרְאוּ וְרָעֲדוּ. אָמְרוּ: "אֲנַחְנוּ יְרֵאוֹת! אֵיפֹה הָרֹעֶה שֶׁלָּנוּ?"

### The Shepherd Sees the Danger

![The young shepherd boy looking intently toward the wolf, his hand shading his eyes to see better, with a concerned but brave expression, Hebrew text "רואה" (seeing) visible](young-shepherd-boy-looking-intently-wolf-hand-shading-eyes-concerned-brave-expression-hebrew-text-roeh-seeing)

רָאָה שִׁמְעוֹן אֶת הַזְּאֵב. רָאָה הָרֹעֶה אֶת הַכְּבָשִׂים הַיְּרֵאוֹת. קָרָא שִׁמְעוֹן: "רְאִיתִי אֶת הַזְּאֵב! אֲנִי רֹאֶה אוֹתוֹ עַכְשָׁו!"

### The Shepherd Is Not Afraid

![The shepherd standing tall and confident, holding his staff firmly, showing no fear as he faces toward the direction of the wolf, with Hebrew text "לא ירא" (not afraid) visible](shepherd-standing-tall-confident-holding-staff-firmly-no-fear-facing-wolf-direction-hebrew-text-lo-yarei)

שִׁמְעוֹן לֹא יָרֵא מִן הַזְּאֵב. הָרֹעֶה לֹא יָרֵא כִּי הוּא אַמִּיץ. אָמַר: "אֲנִי לֹא אִירָא! אֲנִי אֶרְעֶה אֶת הַצֹּאן וְאַצִּיל אוֹתָן!"

### The Shepherd Protects His Flock

![The shepherd bravely walking toward the wolf while his sheep follow behind him, showing his protective role as he shepherds them to safety, with Hebrew text "רועה" (shepherding) visible](shepherd-bravely-walking-toward-wolf-sheep-following-behind-protective-role-shepherding-safety-hebrew-text-roeh-shepherding)

רָעָה שִׁמְעוֹן אֶת הַכְּבָשִׂים אֶל מָקוֹם בָּטוּחַ. הוּא רֹעֶה אוֹתָן בַּחֶסֶד. הַכְּבָשִׂים רָאוּ שֶׁהָרֹעֶה מֵגֵן עֲלֵיהֶן. הֵן רָאוּ וְלֹא יָרְאוּ עוֹד.

### The Lesson About Fear and Courage

![The shepherd sitting with his sheep under a tree, teaching them, with some sheep listening attentively while others graze peacefully, showing the lesson about overcoming fear](shepherd-sitting-sheep-under-tree-teaching-some-listening-attentively-others-grazing-peacefully-overcoming-fear)

אָמַר שִׁמְעוֹן לַכְּבָשִׂים: "רְאִיתֶן אֶת הַזְּאֵב וִירֵאתֶן. זֶה טוֹב - לִרְאוֹת סַכָּנָה. אֲבָל אֲנִי הָרֹעֶה שֶׁלָּכֶן. אֲנִי רֹאֶה כָּל דָּבָר וְרֹעֶה אֶתְכֶן בְּאַהֲבָה."

### Peace Returns

![The shepherd and his flock resting peacefully on the hillside as the sun sets, with the wolf nowhere to be seen, showing how good shepherding brings peace and safety](shepherd-flock-resting-peacefully-hillside-sunset-wolf-nowhere-seen-good-shepherding-peace-safety)

אַחֲרֵי כֵן שָׁבוּ הַכְּבָשִׂים לִרְעוֹת בְּשָׁלוֹם. רָעוּ בְּלִי פַחַד. שִׁמְעוֹן רָעָה אוֹתָן וְהֵן לֹא יָרְאוּ. רָאוּ הַכְּבָשִׂים שֶׁהָרֹעֶה טוֹב וְנֶאֱמָן.

## Vocabulary

### Nouns
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| רֹעֶה | shepherd |
| צֹאן | flock |
| כֶּבֶשׂ/כְּבָשִׂים | sheep/lambs |
| כִּבְשָׂה | ewe |
| זְאֵב | wolf |
| הָר | mountain |
| סַכָּנָה | danger |
| מָקוֹם | place |
| חֶסֶד | kindness |
| אַהֲבָה | love |
| פַּחַד | fear |
| שָׁלוֹם | peace |

### Proper Names
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| שִׁמְעוֹן | Shimon |

### Adjectives
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| צָעִיר | young |
| רָחוֹק | distant |
| בָּטוּחַ | safe |
| אַמִּיץ | brave |
| יָרֵא/יְרֵאָה | afraid (m/f) |
| נֶאֱמָן | faithful |

### Verbs (Roots)
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| ראה | see |
| ירא | fear |
| רעה | shepherd, pasture |
| רעד | tremble |
| צלל | save |
| מגן | protect |
| שׁוב | return |

### Particles/Adverbs
| Hebrew | English |
|--------|---------|
| עוֹד | still, yet |
| אַחֲרֵי כֵן | afterwards |
| בְּלִי | without |

## Grammar

- Contrast between three similar-looking verb roots: ראה (see), ירא (fear), רעה (shepherd)
- Past tense forms of these verbs with different subjects
- Feminine plural forms (יְרֵאוֹת)
- Negative constructions with לֹא
- Participle forms as present tense (רֹעֶה, רֹאֶה)
- Object suffixes on verbs (אוֹתוֹ, אוֹתָן, אֶתְכֶן)
- Relative clauses with שֶׁ
